      • unclosedParentTagClosedBeforeChild

        public void unclosedParentTagClosedBeforeChild()
        will test <x> <a> <b> <b> </x> </a> </x> . Here x is the first tag to be closed thus rendering the next close of a (</a>) to be disregarded.

      • unmatchedTagDoesNotInfluenceStructure

        public void unmatchedTagDoesNotInfluenceStructure()
        <x> <a> <b> <b> </z> </a> </x> An unmatched closing of 'z' appears randomly in the document. This should be disregarded and structure of children and parents should not be influenced. in other words </a> should close the first <a> tag , </x> should close the first <x>, etc.

      • unclosedStartTagWithUnmatchedCloseOfDifferentTag

        public void unclosedStartTagWithUnmatchedCloseOfDifferentTag()
        <a> <x> <a> <b> <b> </z> </a> </x> An unmatched closing of 'z' appears randomly in the document. This should be disregarded and structure of children and parents should not be influenced. Also un unclosed <a> tag appears at the start of the document
